# Namespace: `neurforge` (not `utu`)

The product import namespace is **`neurforge`** (import == distribution == env prefix == brand).
`neurforge` is currently a forwarding shim (`neurforge/__init__.py`) that re-exports the
legacy `utu` package, so `neurforge.X` and `utu.X` resolve to the SAME module object.

## Rules

- New code MUST import from `neurforge.*` (e.g. `from neurforge.tools.base import AsyncBaseToolkit`).
- There is NO Python stdlib named `utu`; ignore any such concern.
- Do NOT delete or physically move the `utu/` package yet (deferred, high-risk phase).
- Do NOT change `neurforge/__init__.py` (the forwarding shim) without good reason.

## Do NOT touch (false-positive `utu` substrings)

- `youtu` / `youtube` / `youtu_agent` (URLs, prompt text, upstream attribution)
- config name `utu-base`; env vars `UTU_*` / `NEURFORGE_*`
- logger name `"utu"`, `utu.log`, `/tmp/utu/...`, `__utu_turn_counter`, `utu_input_filter`
- filesystem paths `DIR_ROOT / "utu" / "prompts"` and `.../"data"` (data still lives in `utu/`)
- LICENSE / NOTICE / upstream attribution

## Frontend UI wheel

The UI wheel is now `neurforge_agent_ui` (was `utu_agent_ui`); reference it as
`resources.files("neurforge_agent_ui.static")`. Rebuild via `frontend/webui/build.sh`.
